            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " to move the case out of California state court to federal court because some fossil fuel extraction takes place in the ocean, which falls under federal court jurisdiction, the appeals court rejected the move. “This is another big, but not surprising, loss for the oil and gas majors,” said Richard Wiles, the President of the Center for Climate Integrity, in response to the ruling. “Three federal appeals courts have now agreed that their arguments to escape accountability in state court do not pass muster. This ruling is a major victory for these California communities seeking their day in court against corporate polluters that spent decades lying about their products’ role in fueling the climate crisis.”",
